{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17511988","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17511988"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:48:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:48:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11825"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11825","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11825"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.37,0.56,0.01,0.02,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4430"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96389"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4430"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11825"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79038"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"147"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"1142"},{"type":"tags","id":"2506"},{"type":"tags","id":"2702"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11635"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6341"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6757"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15081"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32456"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33017"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43274"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96389"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 26-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-week history of intermittent dry cough, wheeze and breathlessness. He denies any history of similar symptoms. He complains that this has recently begun to affect his work. He was previously employed as a carpenter but began work as a panel beater two months ago. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. He has not travelled recently. He smoked 1-2 cigarettes per day when he was 14 years old but has not smoked since. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Respiratory examination reveals scattered expiratory wheeze.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hypersensitivity pneumonitis","Occupational asthma","Allergic rhinitis","Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease","Sarcoidosis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient\u0027s presentation of dry cough, wheeze, and breathlessness that began after starting a new job as a panel beater is highly suggestive of \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccupational\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Easthma\u003C/strong\u003E. The temporal relationship between exposure at work and onset of symptoms is a key feature. In panel beaters, exposure to isocyanates in spray paint is a common trigger for occupational asthma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypersensitivity pneumonitis\u003C/strong\u003E is another occupational lung disease, but it typically presents with chronic breathlessness, cough, and systemic symptoms like fever and weight loss. It is usually caused by repeated exposure to organic dusts, such as from birds or molds. The acute onset and absence of systemic symptoms make this less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAllergic rhinitis\u003C/strong\u003E often coexists with asthma and can be triggered by occupational exposures. However, it is characterised by nasal symptoms such as sneezing, rhinorrhea, and nasal itching, which are not described in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD)\u003C/strong\u003E is a progressive lung disease caused by chronic exposure to cigarette smoke or other noxious particles. It typically occurs in older individuals with a significant smoking history. Given this patient\u0027s young age and minimal smoking history, COPD is highly unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESarcoidosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a multisystem granulomatous disorder that can cause pulmonary symptoms. However, it usually presents with insidious onset of cough, dyspnea, and fatigue, often accompanied by extrapulmonary manifestations. The acute onset after a change in work environment points more towards an occupational cause like asthma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn any patient presenting with new-onset respiratory symptoms, a detailed occupational history is crucial. Patients often do not recognise the potential role of workplace exposures in their illness. Identifying and avoiding the causative agent is a key part of management in occupational asthma.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["An occupational history is essential for a variety of conditions as patients often don\u0027t recognise their workplace as a possible causative factor.","Occupational asthma can be triggered by exposure to various substances including spray paint, flour dust, and animal dander.","A temporal relationship between exposure at work and onset of respiratory symptoms is suggestive of occupational asthma."],"references":["Lau A, Tarlo SM. Update on the Management of Occupational Asthma and Work-Exacerbated Asthma. Allergy Asthma Immunol Res. 2019 Mar;11(2):188-200. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30661311/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79038"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11825"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79038","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/79038"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-01T10:37:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-01T10:39:26+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4430"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96389"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"27","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/27"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc77","name":"Occupational/Environmental Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"}